üöÄ One-click setup (bash script)

  This repo ships with a helper script that:
  
  enables CORS on Tomcat (idempotent),
  
  creates an RDF4J repo,
  
  uploads the RDFS schema and dynamic instance TTLs,
  
  prints the SPARQL endpoint and opens Workbench.
  
  Files expected at repo root:
  
  hackathon-bootstrap.sh
  
  simap-rdfs-schema.ttl
  
  pwe3-dynamic-topology.ttl
  
  Prerequisites
  
  Java 11+
  
  Apache Tomcat with RDF4J Server + Workbench deployed
  (e.g., rdf4j-server.war, rdf4j-workbench.war in TOMCAT_HOME/webapps)
  
  curl (included with Git Bash / macOS / most Linux)

ü™ü Windows (Git Bash) ‚Äì safe & quick
  1) Open Git Bash in the repo root
  chmod +x hackathon-bootstrap.sh
  
  2) Run a safe test (does NOT touch your existing repos)
  ./hackathon-bootstrap.sh --test
    Creates repo: ietf-core-test
    Skips Tomcat restart (Windows-safe)
  
  
  If you need to restart Tomcat on Windows, do it manually in CMD:
  
    cd /d D:\Apps\apache-tomcat-9.0.106\bin
    shutdown.bat
    startup.bat

  Then re-run the script (optional):

    ./hackathon-bootstrap.sh --test

üçéüêß macOS / Linux
  chmod +x hackathon-bootstrap.sh
    If Tomcat lives here:
  TOMCAT_HOME=/opt/tomcat ./hackathon-bootstrap.sh
    or create a safe test repo:
  TOMCAT_HOME=/opt/tomcat ./hackathon-bootstrap.sh --test
  
What the script does

  Adds a CorsFilter to TOMCAT_HOME/conf/web.xml (if missing).

  (By default on Windows) skips Tomcat restart to avoid path issues.

  Bypasses proxies for localhost.

  Deletes any existing repo with the same ID, then creates a fresh NativeStore.

  Uploads:

    simap-rdfs-schema.ttl --> context <http://www.huawei.com/graph/schema>

    pwe3-dynamic-topology.ttl --> context <http://www.huawei.com/graph/instance/pwe3-dynamic-topology>

| Setting          | Default                                      | How to override                                                                   |
| ---------------- | -------------------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Repository ID    | `ietf-core` (`--test` uses `ietf-core-test`) | `REPO_ID=my-repo ./hackathon-bootstrap.sh`                                        |
| Tomcat home      | `/opt/tomcat`                                | `TOMCAT_HOME="/d/Apps/apache-tomcat-9.0.106" ./hackathon-bootstrap.sh`            |
| RDF4J server URL | `http://localhost:8080/rdf4j-server`         | `RDF4J_BASE="http://host:port/rdf4j-server" ./hackathon-bootstrap.sh`             |
| Workbench URL    | `http://localhost:8080/rdf4j-workbench`      | `WORKBENCH_URL="http://host:port/rdf4j-workbench" ./hackathon-bootstrap.sh`       |
| Restart Tomcat   | **skip** (safe)                              | `./hackathon-bootstrap.sh --restart` (macOS/Linux) or restart manually on Windows |

Verify it worked

  After the script finishes it prints:
  
  Workbench
  http://localhost:8080/rdf4j-workbench/repositories/<REPO_ID>/summary
  
  SPARQL endpoint (use this in SPARQLWorks)
  http://localhost:8080/rdf4j-server/repositories/<REPO_ID>

Quick count (optional):

  SELECT (COUNT(*) AS ?n) WHERE { ?s ?p ?o }

Use with SPARQLWorks (visuals)

  Paste the endpoint into SPARQLWorks, then run any of the CONSTRUCT queries from the README (Links --> Nodes/TPs, supporting-link, supporting-node/TP, etc.).

Troubleshooting üõ†Ô∏è

  POST not supported / odd 4xx/5xx via curl
  Your curl may be using a proxy. The script sets no_proxy=localhost, but if running commands manually add --noproxy localhost.
  
  Tomcat restart fails in Git Bash
  This is a Windows path quirk. Use --test (skips restart) and restart Tomcat from CMD:
  
  cd /d %TOMCAT_HOME%\bin && shutdown.bat && startup.bat
  
  
  Workbench opens but repo is missing
  Re-run with --test and watch the ‚ÄúCreating repository ‚Ä¶‚Äù step.
  You can also list repos:
  
  curl --noproxy localhost -s http://localhost:8080/rdf4j-server/repositories \
    | sed -n 's:.*<id>\(.*\)</id>.*:\1:p'

GitHub quick start for others
git clone <your-repo-url>
cd <repo>
chmod +x hackathon-bootstrap.sh
./hackathon-bootstrap.sh --test
  Workbench: http://localhost:8080/rdf4j-workbench/repositories/ietf-core-test/summary
  Endpoint : http://localhost:8080/rdf4j-server/repositories/ietf-core-test
